cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with SAT Modulo Theories, which involves logical constraints in SAT theories combined with theory operations defined over non-Boolean variables. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as SMT solvers are commonly used in AI applications such as automated planning and verification. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possibility as the paper involves the formulation of Symmetry Breaking Predicates (SBPs) which are constraints imposed on the SAT solving part of the SMT solver. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possibility as the paper deals with reducing the search space for SAT solving, which is a fundamental problem in algorithms and data structures. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possibility as the paper involves the implementation of the SBP ideas on top of CVC4, which is a state-of-the-art SMT solver.
